Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.28,0:00:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to JW Broadcasting! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.05,0:00:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This month we’ll consider \Nways we can get \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.66,0:00:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the most benefit \Nfrom Bible principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.13,0:00:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are some highlights: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.23,0:00:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How can Bible study and meditation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,prepare us for trials? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.30,0:00:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll learn about the example \Nof Sister Gertrud Pötzinger \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.37,0:00:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,through an archived interview. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.37,0:00:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What principles and Bible accounts \Nenabled her and her husband, Martin, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.34,0:00:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep their integrity \Nin Nazi Germany?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.01,0:00:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah urges us \Nto seek first the Kingdom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.08,0:00:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What can happen when a person \Nseeks things in the world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.89,0:00:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of the Kingdom? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.22,0:00:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll listen to how this young sister \Nlearned to trust Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.06,0:00:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and lead a life that brings \Ntrue happiness.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.06,0:00:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever thought \Nthat a familiar piece of Bible counsel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.77,0:00:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,didn’t apply to your situation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.24,0:00:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how can analyzing such counsel \Nlead to related principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.61,0:00:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that fit your specific challenge? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.84,0:01:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see \Nin this encouraging dramatization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.71,0:01:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re watching \NJW Broadcasting for February 2017.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.14,0:01:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I make a lot of decisions every day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.84,0:01:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, some have a little impact on our lives; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.64,0:01:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,others have a very big impact. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.31,0:01:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can appreciate that we can make \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.55,0:01:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,choices and decisions for ourselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.39,0:01:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of how life would be \Nif you made no decisions for yourself\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.06,0:01:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,—someone tells you when to go to bed,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.93,0:01:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,they pick out your clothes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.93,0:01:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and they tell you what to do for work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.93,0:01:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, none of us would like that!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.83,0:01:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave each of us free will, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.40,0:02:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s the precious gift \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.50,0:02:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of making choices for ourselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.01,0:02:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, have you ever thought \Nabout why Jehovah gave us this gift? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.31,0:02:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, \Nwhy trust us with free will \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.08,0:02:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,when he knew that we could make \Nbad choices or decisions? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.98,0:02:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one powerful reason is love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.12,0:02:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way to give us the gift of love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.32,0:02:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is also to give us the gift of free will. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.26,0:02:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The two are tied together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.33,0:02:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You really can’t have \None without the other.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.00,0:02:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Nif I programmed my computer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.97,0:02:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to give me a message \Nevery day at 2:00 p.m.: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.44,0:02:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“John, I love you. \NI think you’re a wonderful guy,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.51,0:02:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I think there’d be a little something \Nwrong with me if I thought: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.88,0:02:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Aw, isn’t that nice? \NMy computer, it loves me.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.65,0:02:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, love only exists \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.08,0:02:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,if it comes truly \Nfrom a free-will expression.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.42,0:02:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, did Jehovah place \Nany boundaries on free will? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.56,0:02:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.33,0:02:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They were stated in the Law \Nto the nation of Israel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.06,0:03:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus later repeated them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.73,0:03:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at Matthew 22:37-40: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.17,0:03:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“He said to him: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.74,0:03:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘“You must love Jehovah your God \Nwith your whole heart \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.41,0:03:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘“and with your whole soul\Nand with your whole mind.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.95,0:03:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘This is the greatest\Nand first commandment.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.05,0:03:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘The second, like it, is this: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.35,0:03:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘“You must love your\Nneighbor as yourself.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.36,0:03:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘On these two commandments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.06,0:03:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole Law hangs,\Nand the Prophets.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.63,0:03:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So our use of free will \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.53,0:03:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,has love of God\Nand love of neighbor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.27,0:03:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,as its boundaries.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.27,0:03:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice, for example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.27,0:03:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,what people are doing \Nin this picture, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.74,0:03:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,both inside the circle boundary \Nand outside. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.75,0:03:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,See, free will allows us to do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.81,0:03:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,any of the things \Nwe see in the picture. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.92,0:03:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But love of God \Nand love of neighbor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.95,0:03:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,move us to reject \Nwhat’s outside the circle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.62,0:04:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and choose \Nto do the kinds of things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.66,0:04:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that we see inside the circle.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.13,0:04:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to stay \Nwithin those boundaries, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.13,0:04:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave us \Na marvelous brain \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.30,0:04:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and a built-in conscience, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.47,0:04:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but he also knows \Nwe need more help. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.84,0:04:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s why \Nhe also gave us Bible principles\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.07,0:04:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,—basic truths from the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.14,0:04:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that can help us \Nto make good decisions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.81,0:04:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And it can safely be said \Nthat any decision we face \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.45,0:04:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,can be guided \Nby Bible principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.79,0:04:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, our Creator, Jehovah, \Nknows what’s best for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.59,0:04:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And he also trusts us \Nto make decisions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.93,0:04:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,based on Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.33,0:04:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because he knows \Nthat when we do that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.66,0:04:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,then we’re really, \Ntruly going to be happy, content, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.03,0:04:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and at peace with him \Nand with others.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.54,0:04:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So in review so far: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.64,0:04:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave us free will\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.04,0:04:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,—that’s the privilege \Nto make choices for ourselves—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.51,0:04:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and he also gave us \NBible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.95,0:05:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,as the boundaries \Nto our choices. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.89,0:05:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But making difficult decisions \Nrequires that we train ourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.42,0:05:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to recognize Bible principles \Nand apply them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.76,0:05:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s read Romans 12:1, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.00,0:05:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s see how this verse \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.07,0:05:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,describes the decision-making process. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.54,0:05:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, I appeal to you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.54,0:05:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“by the compassions of God, brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.54,0:05:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“to present your bodies \Nas a living sacrifice, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.08,0:05:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“holy and acceptable to God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.82,0:05:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a sacred service \Nwith your power of reason.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.82,0:05:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So are we using \Nour “power of reason” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.33,0:05:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand Bible principles? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.66,0:05:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, young children \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.80,0:05:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,ask lots of questions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.20,0:05:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But has a child ever asked you: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.34,0:05:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“What happens when I drop a ball? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.51,0:05:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,a pencil? a book?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.97,0:05:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they don’t ask that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.98,0:06:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They know what happens \Nto anything they drop. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.55,0:06:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It falls down! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the child doesn’t need \Nrules for every object \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.55,0:06:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but has quickly grasped the principle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.55,0:06:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything he drops falls down. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.22,0:06:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, \Nwhat if an 18-year-old asked you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.06,0:06:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“What’s going to happen\Nwhen I drop this pen?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.83,0:06:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s obvious \Nhe’s not been paying attention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.97,0:06:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to basic principles of life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.87,0:06:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So by us paying attention \Nto Bible principles, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.77,0:06:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we can very quickly see \Nthe pattern \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.91,0:06:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of love of God \Nand love of neighbor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and know \Nthe right thing to do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.48,0:06:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,without a long list of rules \Nfor every situation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.95,0:06:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how can we train\Nour “power of reason”?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.42,0:06:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We train it by paying attention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.89,0:06:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,as we read and study the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.80,0:06:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we don’t need rules \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.83,0:07:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,for which movies to watch, \Nwhich songs to listen to, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.37,0:07:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,or what clothes we can wear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.61,0:07:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’re paying attention \Nwhen we’re reading the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.81,0:07:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we train our conscience \Nwith Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.31,0:07:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can make \Nsuch decisions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.45,0:07:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,without needing \Na long list of rules. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.75,0:07:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, \Nwe could compare our training \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.22,0:07:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of our “power of reason” \Nto a blind person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.42,0:07:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,using a guide dog. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.59,0:07:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, an untrained dog \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.60,0:07:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,would be very helpful \Nto a blind person. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.30,0:07:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It would bark when others \Nwere around, for example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.80,0:07:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \Na dog trained \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.04,0:07:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in specific skills \Nis amazingly helpful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.64,0:07:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog knows \Nwhen to stop at curbs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.04,0:07:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and walk around obstacles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.04,0:07:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that the person \Nmight run their head into. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.51,0:07:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A guide dog \Nis also taught a skill called \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.25,0:07:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“intelligent disobedience.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.75,0:07:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if the blind person \Nencourages the dog forward, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.19,0:07:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it won’t obey, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.19,0:07:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’ll pull \Nthe person back from danger. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.06,0:08:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it can take a year or more \Nof training for the dog to learn \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.93,0:08:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the amazing skills \Nthat are so helpful to a blind person.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.04,0:08:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, our raw, \Nuntrained “power of reason” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.17,0:08:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,can help us to a degree. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.21,0:08:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it can be amazing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.25,0:08:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,if we take the time to train it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.25,0:08:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here are \Nthree skills that we can use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.25,0:08:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to train our “power of reason.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.25,0:08:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They are illustrating, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.59,0:08:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,analyzing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.59,0:08:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and balancing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.26,0:08:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to consider our first skill, \Nillustrating, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.16,0:08:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s use the general topic \Nof forgiveness.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.24,0:08:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What Bible principles \Ncould help with forgiveness? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.38,0:08:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Please think of as many principles \Nand scriptures as you can. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.58,0:08:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if it helps, \Nyou can pause the program now \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.95,0:08:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and write down \Nthe principles that come to mind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.45,0:09:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, your list \Nmay include principles like these: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.49,0:09:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew 18:22 says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.96,0:09:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to forgive “up to 77 times”; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.53,0:09:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 12:18 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.00,0:09:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“The tongue of the wise is a healing”; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.00,0:09:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and Colossians 3:13 tells us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.51,0:09:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to ‘forgive one another freely.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.88,0:09:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the skill \Nwe want to learn is illustrating\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.05,0:09:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,—creating a mental picture \Nof an idea or principle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.18,0:09:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to see its real meaning \Nand impact. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.29,0:09:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, even if we \Nare not skilled artists, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.26,0:09:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us can and do create \Npictures in our minds. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.26,0:09:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When illustrating, \Npay attention to things that are similar \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.93,0:09:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or like the thing \Nyou are trying to visualize. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.00,0:09:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Nif sin is like debt, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.01,0:09:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,then forgiveness \Nis like someone canceling the debt. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.68,0:09:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If a hurtful remark \Nis like a cut, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.98,0:10:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,then forgiveness \Nis like seeing it heal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.82,0:10:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If sin is like a mark \Non a blackboard, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.35,0:10:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiveness is like erasing it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.69,0:10:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 12:18 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.96,0:10:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is a great example \Nof using the “like” technique. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.37,0:10:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“Thoughtless speech \Nis like the stabs of a sword, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.44,0:10:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but the tongue of the wise \Nis a healing.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.94,0:10:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine what your skin \Nwould look like \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.94,0:10:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if you still had \Nevery open cut, bruise, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.15,0:10:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,or bleeding scratch \Nsince childhood. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.65,0:10:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,See, Jehovah \Nwonderfully designed our body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.52,0:10:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to heal such minor cuts \Nand bruises. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.29,0:10:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can now visualize \Nhow the forgiveness of others \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.36,0:10:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,helps us to heal emotionally. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.93,0:10:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, learning to illustrate, \Nor visualize, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.30,0:10:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,takes time and practice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.30,0:10:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it can be one \Nof the most powerful skills we use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.70,0:10:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to train \Nour “power of reason,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.87,0:10:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and it can also be \Nquite enjoyable. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.11,0:11:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, \Ntry at your family worship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.21,0:11:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to take \Nthe principles for a topic \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.68,0:11:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and see \Nhow many similarities, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.98,0:11:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or “likes,” \Nyou can come up with. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.32,0:11:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, granted, \Nthey all won’t be amazing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.09,0:11:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but you may be surprised \Nby the insights \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.16,0:11:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that come from seeing \Nsomething from a new perspective.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.19,0:11:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s consider now \Nour second skill: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.66,0:11:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,analyzing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.76,0:11:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, analyzing something means \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.03,0:11:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“examining it carefully in detail.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.90,0:11:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And let’s use \Nthe topic of wrong desires. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.41,0:11:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in this case, \Nlet’s say that we’ve already found \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.28,0:11:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the principle \Nat Colossians 3:5: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.32,0:11:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Deaden, therefore, your body members \Nthat are on the earth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.99,0:11:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“as respects sexual immorality, \Nuncleanness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.59,0:11:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“uncontrolled sexual passion, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.96,0:11:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“hurtful desire, and greediness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.46,0:11:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which is idolatry.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.96,0:11:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what can we learn\Nfrom analyzing Colossians 3:5\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.87,0:12:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to help when we struggle \Nwith wrong desires? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.04,0:12:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, feel free \Nto pause the program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.84,0:12:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if you want some time \Nto think about it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.61,0:12:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Look carefully \Nat each step outlined. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.15,0:12:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice, for example, \Nwhat appears to be \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.15,0:12:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,a reverse order \Nof the steps leading to sin? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.99,0:12:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This verse works its way \Nfrom sexual immorality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.73,0:12:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,back to the very roots \Nof the problem.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.33,0:12:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s take each phrase \Nstarting with the last, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.60,0:12:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“greediness, which is idolatry.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.44,0:12:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, sexual immorality \Nstarts with selfishness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.64,0:12:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,greedily putting our needs \Nahead of anything else. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.14,0:12:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is “hurtful desire.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.31,0:12:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Greediness leads to “hurtful desire.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.88,0:12:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s like a person \Nhanging around a bakery, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.05,0:12:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,smelling the bread and cakes \Nwhen he can’t pay for it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.56,0:12:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, \Nhanging around immoral entertainment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.93,0:13:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or bad associates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.93,0:13:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,can feed “hurtful desire” \Nfor what is not ours. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.44,0:13:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is listed \N“uncontrolled sexual passion.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.94,0:13:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So “hurtful desire” \Nhas now turned from an idea \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.44,0:13:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,into a strong emotion \Nof passion, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.45,0:13:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,causing one \Nto look for an opportunity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.95,0:13:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to fulfill the desire. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.62,0:13:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, “uncleanness.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.36,0:13:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The previous steps have now led \Nto inappropriate physical conduct \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.66,0:13:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,with another person. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.90,0:13:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, “sexual immorality”\N—serious sin. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.63,0:13:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Sexual immorality \Nhas occurred between persons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.54,0:13:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that are not married \Nto one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.51,0:13:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So analyzing Colossians 3:5 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.58,0:13:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,can really help us to eliminate, \Nnot stimulate, wrong desires. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.48,0:13:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can see \Nhow important it is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.95,0:13:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to get rid \Nof wrong desires immediately. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.49,0:13:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s easier \Nto walk away from sin \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.49,0:14:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when we’re still in the early stages, \Nrather than later.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.03,0:14:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need \Nto practice the skill \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.19,0:14:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of not simply \Njust reading scriptures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.50,0:14:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but analyzing them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.50,0:14:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,until we’ve learned \Nall that we can. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.67,0:14:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can use \Nthe many research tools we have \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to find valuable comments \Nand application.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.91,0:14:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s consider our third \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.88,0:14:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and final skill: balancing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.01,0:14:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.02,0:14:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s use a question \Non the topic of alcohol.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What Bible principles \Ncould help a couple to decide \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.79,0:14:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,whether to serve alcohol \Nat their wedding? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.39,0:14:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What principles and scriptures \Ndo you think would help them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.16,0:14:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,make a balanced decision? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.27,0:14:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, you’re welcome \Nto pause the program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.57,0:14:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,if you’d like to write down \Nwhat comes to mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.94,0:14:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,or to research something. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.74,0:14:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, your list probably has \Nsome of these principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.61,0:15:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,At John 2:9, \NJesus made wine for a wedding. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.45,0:15:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \N1 Corinthians 6:10 says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.25,0:15:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that ‘drunkards \Nwill not inherit the Kingdom.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.62,0:15:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And 1 Corinthians 10:31, 32 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.36,0:15:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whether you are eating or drinking . . . , \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.03,0:15:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,do all things for God’s glory” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.53,0:15:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and to “keep from becoming \Ncauses for stumbling.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.94,0:15:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, \Nit doesn’t seem \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.94,0:15:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that any one principle \Nprovides the answer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.58,0:15:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The couple could simply say: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.58,0:15:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, Jesus served wine at a wedding, \Nso we can too.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.21,0:15:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there’s really more \Nto it than that, isn’t there? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.12,0:15:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s clear that a balance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.79,0:15:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of all these Bible principles \Nis needed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.66,0:15:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Will relatives \Nor others be there \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.36,0:15:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,who might be prone \Nto overdrinking? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.96,0:15:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Would serving alcohol bother \Nthe conscience of many present \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.80,0:15:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because of local customs \Nand feelings about alcohol? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.97,0:15:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s often the case \Nwhen making decisions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.81,0:16:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that we need to balance \Nseveral Bible principles, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.54,0:16:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,not taking any one principle solely \Non its own merit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.31,0:16:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah expects us \Nto use our “power of reason” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.18,0:16:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to balance Bible principles \Nand make good decisions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.46,0:16:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecclesiastes 7:16-18 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.09,0:16:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,gives us good advice \Nabout being balanced. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.06,0:16:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be overly righteous, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.37,0:16:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“nor show yourself excessively wise. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.40,0:16:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why should you bring ruin to yourself? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.07,0:16:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be excessively wicked, \Nnor be foolish. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.28,0:16:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why should you die before your time? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.41,0:16:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is best to grasp one warning \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.45,0:16:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“without letting go of the other; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.45,0:16:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for the one who fears God \Nwill heed them both.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.35,0:16:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How true. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.46,0:16:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Such balance between extremes \Nis often necessary \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.89,0:16:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when we apply \NBible principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.96,0:16:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to heed them both, \Nso to speak. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.90,0:16:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to balance \Nall the Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.33,0:17:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can come \Nto the decision \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.34,0:17:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that would show love of God \Nand love of neighbor. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.84,0:17:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We could illustrate the balance \Nbetween different Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.18,0:17:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and applying them with this model bike. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.05,0:17:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a gift from a brother in Malawi. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.42,0:17:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a bicycle has \Nthree basic principles of operation: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.59,0:17:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the brakes, the pedals, and the steering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.66,0:17:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the brakes are really like principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.19,0:17:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that slow us down \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.20,0:17:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,or stop us from doing the wrong thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.33,0:17:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And the pedals are really like the principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.53,0:17:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that move us forward \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.53,0:17:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in showing love for Jehovah \Nand our brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.50,0:17:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the steering is like our free will \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.64,0:17:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to choose a direction in life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.28,0:17:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that pleases Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.28,0:17:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So making decisions \Nis like riding a bicycle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.35,0:17:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to balance \Nseveral Bible principles.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.39,0:17:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So in review, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.56,0:17:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave us free will \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.92,0:17:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to use within the boundaries \Nof love of God and love of neighbor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.46,0:18:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and many other fine Bible principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.36,0:18:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Making difficult decisions requires \Nthat we train our “power of reason” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.27,0:18:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to recognize Bible principles \Nand apply them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.04,0:18:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And we discussed \Nhow to train \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.07,0:18:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,our power of reason \Nwith the three skills: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.24,0:18:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,illustrating, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.71,0:18:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,analyzing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.01,0:18:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and balancing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.31,0:18:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So no matter what decisions \Nyou are faced with, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.38,0:18:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we encourage you: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.38,0:18:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let Bible principles guide you.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.26,0:18:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s use \Nthe following dramatization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.36,0:18:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to practice the skills \Nwe’ve just discussed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.26,0:18:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In this video, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.26,0:18:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,three Witnesses all hear \Nthe same familiar Bible counsel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.10,0:18:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,at a Christian meeting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.10,0:18:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And at first, \Nit doesn’t seem to apply \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.40,0:18:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to anything \Nthey’re currently experiencing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.77,0:18:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but it does. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.77,0:18:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that’s happened to you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.94,0:18:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,As you listen to their reasoning, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.18,0:18:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you think they \Ncould do to let Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.62,0:18:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,guide them \Nto making a good decision?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.96,0:19:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We must know Jehovah well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.29,0:19:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That means knowing \Nhis thinking on matters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.89,0:19:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We should welcome \Nsuch an examination \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.67,0:19:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and make any necessary changes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.50,0:19:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.54,0:19:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s read \N1 Corinthians 15:33 together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.41,0:19:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we read: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.48,0:19:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be misled. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.51,0:19:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad associations spoil useful habits.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.15,0:19:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,As familiar as that principle is, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.12,0:19:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,can you think of an area in your life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.92,0:19:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,where it’s difficult to apply?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.66,0:19:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, John.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.76,0:19:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.40,0:19:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it’s not your usual, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.53,0:19:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but there’s no one to entertain \Nthose clients tonight. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.07,0:19:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So can you do it? \NThanks.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.07,0:19:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have. . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.57,0:19:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Great.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.61,0:19:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, \Nit wasn’t my usual thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.29,0:20:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I need to support my family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.30,0:20:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And these aren’t really my friends. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.97,0:20:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I can handle it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.67,0:20:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I think.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.60,0:20:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .we’re faced with bad associations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.71,0:20:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in subtle ways. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.74,0:20:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This may require us \Nto ask additional questions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.48,0:20:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of ourselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.48,0:20:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we letting in bad association \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.78,0:20:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,through social media? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.12,0:20:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps we can think \Nof another way bad association. . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.49,0:20:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t think so\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.63,0:20:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,—except for some friends \Nfrom my old congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.76,0:20:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.77,0:20:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re not doing so well spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.30,0:20:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I stay connected \Nand see what they’re doing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.34,0:20:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe I can help them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.11,0:21:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .can affect us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.58,0:21:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it’s something very specific. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.91,0:21:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.95,0:21:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,bad association \Nis coming from a place \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.68,0:21:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we never expected.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.12,0:21:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I only join games \Nwith Witness friends I know. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.26,0:21:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But sometimes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.33,0:21:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they connect \Nwith people I don’t know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.34,0:21:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who pick games \NI’m not sure we should play. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.68,0:21:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But maybe my friends know them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.81,0:21:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so they’re probably OK.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.05,0:21:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It is vital that we avoid \Nbad associations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.82,0:21:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, \Nas we resume in Psalm 26. . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.89,0:21:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic principle in this story\Nis one we all know: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.83,0:21:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Bad associations spoil useful habits.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.00,0:21:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But do our three friends \Nfind themselves in the same situation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.74,0:22:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,where they can simply apply \N1 Corinthians 15:33 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.11,0:22:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in exactly the same way? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.14,0:22:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.14,0:22:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The family head is concerned \Nabout supporting his family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.08,0:22:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Our sister wants \Nto stay in touch with her friends \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.72,0:22:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in hopes of helping them spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.32,0:22:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And our young brother \Ndidn’t know exactly who \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.15,0:22:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,his associates were.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.52,0:22:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you already thinking of \Nadditional principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.76,0:22:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that would apply \Nto each person’s problem? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.50,0:22:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you illustrate, analyze, \Nor balance those principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.93,0:22:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,if you were in their position? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.04,0:22:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to, \Npause the program here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.94,0:22:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the time to write down \Nwhat you’re thinking. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.04,0:22:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then watch how they each \Nsearch for Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.91,0:22:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and train their “power of reason.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.95,0:22:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that talk \Ndidn’t apply to me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.85,0:22:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But can I really handle \Nbad association?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.52,0:22:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If I take a stand, \NI may lose my job.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.70,0:23:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But that’s being anxious \Nabout tomorrow. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.24,0:23:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.87,0:23:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“So never be anxious and say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.58,0:23:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘What are we to eat?’ or, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.74,0:23:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘What are we to drink?’ or, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.14,0:23:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,‘What are we to wear?’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.85,0:23:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah knows I need a job. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.02,0:23:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And I need \Nto set a good example \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.99,0:23:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for when my children \Nface bad association.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.73,0:23:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Corinthians 15:33.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.10,0:23:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My friends’ posts \Nare getting worse\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.20,0:23:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,—their pictures and comments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.71,0:23:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, 2 Timothy 2:16.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.55,0:23:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“But reject empty speeches \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.18,0:23:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“that violate what is holy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.85,0:24:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,for they will lead \Nto more and more ungodliness.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.39,0:24:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m letting them share \N“empty speeches” with me online. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.36,0:24:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I will try to help \Nthem while I still can, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.20,0:24:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but following their posts \Nis not the way to do it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.70,0:24:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I told Mom what’s been happening \Nwhen I game \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.27,0:24:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,with my friends. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.94,0:24:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,She gave me good ideas \Non what to look for \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.08,0:24:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Research Guide.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.28,0:24:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“Christian Life.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.75,0:24:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Association.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.59,0:24:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Is Your Recreation Beneficial?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.09,0:24:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“Who Are My Companions?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.16,0:24:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.90,0:24:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Who are the ones I want \Nto share my leisure time with?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.63,0:24:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“Does he have the same Bible-based \Nvalues and morals that I have?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.74,0:24:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Good question. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.81,0:24:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t even know \Nwho they are sometimes.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.11,0:24:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 119:63 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.31,0:25:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am a friend of all who fear you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.12,0:25:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and of those who keep your orders.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.82,0:25:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I only know them online, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.76,0:25:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t know if they fear Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.63,0:25:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn in our Bibles \Nto the book \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.70,0:25:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of 1 Timothy 1:5 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.97,0:25:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and notice how it reads: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.71,0:25:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“Really, the objective of this instruction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.71,0:25:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“is love out of a clean heart \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.95,0:25:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“and out of a good conscience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.18,0:25:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of faith without hypocrisy.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.35,0:25:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We train our conscience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.39,0:25:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with Bible principles \Nthat reveal Jehovah’s thinking. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.29,0:25:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There may be several principles needed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.33,0:25:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,for our unique problem. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.90,0:25:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we find \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.93,0:25:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and apply them,  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.90,0:25:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll enjoy a clean heart \Nand a good conscience.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.98,0:26:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How did their Bible principles \Nand meditation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.72,0:26:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,compare to what \Nyou were thinking? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.98,0:26:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you may not have come up \Nwith the same scriptures and thoughts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.39,0:26:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but that’s OK. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.39,0:26:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The important thing is that by training \Nour “power of reason,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.49,0:26:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re aligning our thoughts \Nwith Jehovah’s thoughts.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.00,0:26:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see the three skills in use? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.23,0:26:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The young brother was able \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.24,0:26:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to visualize his potential friends. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.57,0:26:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He couldn’t see them literally, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.64,0:26:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but knowing they didn’t fear Jehovah \Nor keep His orders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.48,0:26:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,painted a picture of the kind of associates \Nthey might prove to be.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.98,0:26:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When our sister \Nanalyzed 2 Timothy 2:16, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.82,0:26:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,she saw the social media comments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.56,0:26:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,were similar to “empty speeches” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.92,0:26:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that could weaken her faith.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.93,0:26:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the family head balanced \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.96,0:26:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,his family responsibilities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.50,0:27:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,by applying the principle \Nat Matthew 6:31, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.40,0:27:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,where Jesus said \Nnot to be anxious over material things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.31,0:27:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can imagine him trying \Nto work the matter out with his boss \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.34,0:27:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,while trusting Jehovah \Nto care for him and his family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.75,0:27:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what \Nmight happen to his job.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.78,0:27:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Think now about another principle \Nin Matthew chapter 6. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.89,0:27:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus tells us in verse 33 \Nto ‘seek first the Kingdom.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.83,0:27:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Young ones especially \Nface temptations\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.20,0:27:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,—both large and small—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.40,0:27:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to seek things \Nin the world instead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.73,0:27:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And sadly, some have ignored \NBible principles they have learned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.51,0:27:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ve looked \Nfor happiness in what appears \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.71,0:27:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the exciting possibilities \Nof this system of things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.18,0:27:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In this “Truth Transforms Lives” segment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.35,0:27:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Anneliese Zelina explains \Nwhat led her to a similar choice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.79,0:27:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and what drew her back to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.13,0:28:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Growing up in the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.56,0:28:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like I fit in \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.76,0:28:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,more with my friends at school \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.87,0:28:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,or people who weren’t Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.90,0:28:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I was living a double life \Nand I knew it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.70,0:28:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not baptized.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.04,0:28:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I had always tried to make \Nthe truth fit in with the world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.81,0:28:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And this time I decided \Nthat I just want to give \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.31,0:28:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the world a shot \Nand see what that’s like.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.35,0:28:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I came right to my parents, \Nand I said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.38,0:28:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“I want to move to LA \Nand pursue modeling.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.25,0:28:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I had my first job within the week. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.49,0:28:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It looked so glamorous.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.60,0:28:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There were a lot of parties\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.60,0:28:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—going to the coolest houses, \Ngetting to hang out with celebrities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.84,0:28:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no rules. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.88,0:28:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the money \Nto do whatever you want.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.08,0:28:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That lifestyle was so far \Nfrom what I was raised knowing as right \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.99,0:29:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that I basically had \Nno relationship with Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.86,0:29:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Once all the smoke \Nand mirrors are gone, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.13,0:29:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you see these things \Nfor what they are.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.13,0:29:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember I called my mom, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.13,0:29:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and I told her: \N“It’s like Sodom and Gomorrah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.13,0:29:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m literally in the middle of it all.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.14,0:29:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, like, this is it; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.14,0:29:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,this is what everyone says is the best, \Nand I’m not happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.61,0:29:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just felt so dull\N—empty. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.61,0:29:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I actually thought to myself: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.61,0:29:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I wish—\NI wish I was never raised a Witness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.05,0:29:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I never even knew Jehovah existed.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.15,0:29:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There were certain nights \Nwhere I needed him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.79,0:29:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking, \N‘Just pray; just go to him.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.06,0:29:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I couldn’t.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.49,0:29:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I would never be able to\Ncome back to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.07,0:29:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the jobs \NI got hired to do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.07,0:29:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,was to work \Nfor this young fashion company. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.87,0:29:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In between different outfits and shoots, \Nyou would, you know, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.64,0:29:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,talk with the photographer.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.38,0:29:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what are you guys \Ngoing to be for Halloween?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.41,0:30:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Matt doesn’t celebrate Halloween. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.42,0:30:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.42,0:30:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So am I.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.99,0:30:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not a joke.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.19,0:30:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I’m not kidding. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.19,0:30:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I was raised as a Witness.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.33,0:30:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was raised as one as well.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.56,0:30:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you, um—\Ndo you go to meetings?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.60,0:30:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I haven’t been in forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.06,0:30:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.50,0:30:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, I haven’t.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.50,0:30:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a last-minute job to New York. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.50,0:30:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to walk the Brooklyn Bridge. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.94,0:30:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew Bethel was there, \Nand I’d never been to Bethel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.71,0:30:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This sister stopped me on my tour, \Nand she invited me up to her office. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.18,0:30:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There were different paintings \Nof the resurrection.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.35,0:30:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,She asked me, “Do you know why \Nthe people are waiting on the balcony?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.55,0:30:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was like, \N“I—I don’t know. Why?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.39,0:30:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And she said, “Because they’re waiting \Nfor their loved ones to be resurrected.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.80,0:30:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It was as if something \Njust went straight to my heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.57,0:30:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve never felt something like that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.20,0:30:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I had for the first time actually seen \Nthe resurrection and believed it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.51,0:31:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t just this thing that might happen\N—it was for sure. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.18,0:31:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew exactly \Nwhat it was going to look like. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.18,0:31:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I would be standing there \Non that balcony \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.68,0:31:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for my loved ones \Nto come back, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.65,0:31:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wanted to be there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.65,0:31:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The resurrection was so real to me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.26,0:31:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And the second I got out of Bethel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.69,0:31:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I—I called my mom, \Nand I told her, and I said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.53,0:31:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“Mom, Mom, I’m coming back. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.94,0:31:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“I know exactly what I need to do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.67,0:31:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m coming back to Jehovah.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.61,0:31:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I had made up my mind, you know, \NI’m going to give Jehovah a chance. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.25,0:31:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know, \NI’m coming back to the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.58,0:31:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to do it right.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.12,0:31:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There was an elder \Nwho was doing the Watchtower, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.49,0:31:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and he just came off so kind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.49,0:31:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that I thought, you know, \Nwhen this meeting ends, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.26,0:31:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to talk with him, and I’m going \Nto explain to him why I’m here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.06,0:31:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I had so many changes to make.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.50,0:31:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew 6:33 is so important to me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.80,0:32:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Seek first the Kingdom.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.40,0:32:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,My entire life I sought \Neverything else before Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.41,0:32:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I never put him first, \Nand I for the first time was saying, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.38,0:32:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“OK, Jehovah, I’m going to put you first.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.35,0:32:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The job I have right now \Nisn’t necessarily my dream job, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.75,0:32:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but it allows me to do exactly \Nwhat I want to do for Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.89,0:32:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,—and that’s pioneer.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.96,0:32:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to walk down Hollywood Boulevard \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.46,0:32:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,going from casting to casting \Nwith my portfolio in hand, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.00,0:32:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and now I walk down Hollywood Boulevard \Nwith the cart in my hand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.70,0:32:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Out in the ministry, \NI see models that I used to work with, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.23,0:32:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and I love getting to show \Nthem that this is my new life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.90,0:32:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and this has changed my life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.91,0:32:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I am so happy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.04,0:32:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what it’s like \Nto superficially feel good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.71,0:32:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But to literally have the joy, \Nthe happiness\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.81,0:32:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—I want to share that with everybody.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.39,0:32:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah completely changed my life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.97,0:33:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re so happy \Nthat Sister Zelina returned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.74,0:33:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and dedicated \Nher life to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.98,0:33:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though she wanted to forget \Nwhat she knew about God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.01,0:33:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the things she had learned about him \Nkept coming back to her mind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.98,0:33:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, when she saw \Nthe picture of the resurrection, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.45,0:33:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,while touring Bethel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.46,0:33:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a powerful reminder \Nof Jehovah’s love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.63,0:33:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, \NSister Zelina’s Bible-trained conscience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.23,0:33:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,was at work the entire time.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.43,0:33:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Young ones, please know \Nthat Jehovah does not want \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.07,0:33:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to hold you back \Nfrom having fun, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.47,0:33:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and he doesn’t want \Nyou to feel guilty \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.94,0:33:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for the desire to use \Nyour talents and to enjoy life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.88,0:33:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But he does want to protect you \Nfrom spiritual dangers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.08,0:33:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and he asks you to seek first \Nthe Kingdom in these last days. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.89,0:34:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 10:22 puts it well: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.02,0:34:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is the blessing of Jehovah \Nthat makes one rich, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.46,0:34:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and He adds no pain with it.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.47,0:34:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It is Satan’s system that adds \Nany pain we may experience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.60,0:34:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Zelina and so many others \Nhave found that scripture to be true. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.51,0:34:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So often, young ones who choose \Nto give Jehovah their best \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.98,0:34:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,are blessed with ways to use \Ntheir talents and interests \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.15,0:34:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in sacred service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.28,0:34:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah wants you to be part \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.29,0:34:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the exciting fulfillment \Nof Micah 4:2, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.92,0:34:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,where nations are saying: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.93,0:34:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“Come, let us go up \Nto the mountain of Jehovah.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.60,0:34:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that verse was the daily text \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.37,0:34:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and part of a morning worship discussion \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.80,0:34:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,by Brother Geoffrey Jackson. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.10,0:34:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Micah’s prophecy is being fulfilled now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.27,0:34:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and it results \Nin our worldwide brotherhood \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.48,0:35:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and highlights the need \Nfor Christian unity and neutrality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.15,0:35:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So Brother Jackson asked \Nan interesting question, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.58,0:35:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“How important is our neutrality?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.69,0:35:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true, isn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.29,0:35:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at this prophecy \Nin the book of Micah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.16,0:35:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s very exciting \Nbecause it portrays to us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.63,0:35:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,what’s actually happening \Namong God’s people today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.73,0:35:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that although \Nin the new world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.14,0:35:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,there will be a tremendous unity \Ndisplayed by God’s people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.67,0:35:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,chapter 4 of Micah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.88,0:35:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually portraying  what’s happening now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.61,0:35:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re involved with this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.65,0:35:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that because \Nin verse 5 it says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.72,0:35:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that at the same time \Nthat this unity would be evident: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.82,0:35:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“All the peoples will walk, \Neach in the name of its god.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.62,0:35:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s not talking \Nabout the new world, is it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.29,0:35:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s talking about the time \Nwe are living in now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.50,0:35:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what is it that helps all \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses worldwide \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.33,0:35:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to be so united and not to be involved \Nwith the wars of this world?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.31,0:36:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one of the things that helps us \Nis our Christian neutrality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.64,0:36:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we mean by neutrality? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.71,0:36:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We mean not taking sides \Nin political issues. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.08,0:36:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we take sides \Nwith Jehovah and the Kingdom, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.19,0:36:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but with regard to worldly political debates \Nand issues that arise, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.06,0:36:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we don’t take sides. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.90,0:36:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is this so important? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.13,0:36:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s turn our Bibles \Nto Revelation chapter 13. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.40,0:36:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Revelation 13:16, 17, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.67,0:36:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and here it tells us: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.58,0:36:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“It puts under compulsion all people\N—the small and the great, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.15,0:36:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“the rich and the poor, \Nthe free and the slaves\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.42,0:36:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“—that these should be marked \Non their right hand or on their forehead, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.85,0:36:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“and that nobody can buy or sell \Nexcept a person having the mark, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.69,0:36:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the name of the wild beast \Nor the number of its name.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.03,0:37:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the point of this verse? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.90,0:37:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course, \Nwe will look forward to seeing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.70,0:37:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,how this may \Nturn out in the future \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.17,0:37:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and what pressure is put \Non God’s people at that time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.71,0:37:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But even now, \Nwe see the principle here \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.78,0:37:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that the political system is wanting \Nto put its mark on us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.68,0:37:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,mentally as well as physically. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.85,0:37:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see the forehead \Nas well as the hand being involved. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.82,0:37:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need to be absolutely certain \Nthat we remain neutral \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.70,0:37:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with regard to political issues \Nin the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.70,0:37:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,not only by \Nnot being involved actively \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.07,0:37:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in the political issues \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.07,0:37:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but also mentally not allowing \Nourselves to take sides.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.31,0:37:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What are some of the things \Nthat perhaps could erode our neutrality? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.78,0:37:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe we could mention \Nthree things this morning. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.79,0:37:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,One is the propaganda \Nthat the world puts forward. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.76,0:37:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we have seen what the media says \Nabout Jehovah’s Witnesses, haven’t we? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.83,0:38:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How distorted some of their reports are \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.33,0:38:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they can paint \Na negative picture with regard to us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.20,0:38:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, should we expect \Nthat they are neutral\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.30,0:38:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with regard to other events \Nthat they report on, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.64,0:38:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,particularly when there are conflicts \Nbetween two nations? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.08,0:38:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The media \Nin one particular nation may promote \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.88,0:38:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,certain ideas about the other nation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.55,0:38:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We may be affected by that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.65,0:38:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We may be surprised perhaps \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.96,0:38:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to visit some other countries \Nthat have a different political ideology \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.09,0:38:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and be surprised to see \Nhow things perhaps are a little different \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.76,0:38:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in that country to how it’s portrayed \Nby the media in our country. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.17,0:38:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need to be careful \Nnot to be influenced \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.64,0:38:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,by the propaganda of this world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.11,0:38:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,particularly media reports and so on.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.74,0:38:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s another thing perhaps \Nthat could cause us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.48,0:38:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to lose a measure of neutrality? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.75,0:38:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sporting events. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.75,0:38:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes sporting events \Nare able to achieve \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.52,0:39:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,certain goals \Nwith regard to nationalism. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.16,0:39:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the national anthem \Nbeing played at many of these events. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.06,0:39:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It reminds me many years ago \Nwhen I was in a different country, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.20,0:39:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a friend of mine asked me \Nto record a certain sporting event. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.10,0:39:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn’t particularly \Ninterested in the event, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.60,0:39:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but because he made this request, \NI recorded it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.64,0:39:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, I wanted to make sure \Nthat I got the last ten minutes of it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.64,0:39:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought our friendship \Nmay be strained \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.71,0:39:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,if I didn’t get \Nthe actual last part of the game. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.32,0:39:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,When I watched it, \Nit was absolutely exciting\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.29,0:39:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,—nail-biting finish. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.29,0:39:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, after the brother \Ngave me back the videotape, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.79,0:39:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought maybe \Nsome of the other brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.46,0:39:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,who would be interested \Nin this sporting event \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.56,0:39:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,may want to have it \Nrather than just wipe the tape. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.40,0:39:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So I offered it to several, \Nand each one of them said to me: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.10,0:39:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“No thanks. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.97,0:39:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If we had won, \Nperhaps it would be different.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.51,0:39:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what was the problem? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.64,0:39:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said to them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.81,0:40:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“Were you watching the game \Nor were you taking sides?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.18,0:40:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,An interesting concept, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.18,0:40:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because here \Ntwo different nations were involved. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.22,0:40:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to be careful \Nthat even sporting events \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.02,0:40:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t stir up within us \Ncertain nationalistic feelings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.50,0:40:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and perhaps we could take sides \Nwith regard to certain events.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.10,0:40:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The third area that perhaps \Ncould erode our neutrality: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.81,0:40:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the political promises being made, \Nparticularly at election time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.71,0:40:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps one of the candidates \Nis from our ethnic background \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.62,0:40:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or perhaps \Nis the same gender as we are. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.02,0:40:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at the political situation \Nthese days with many elections, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.29,0:40:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems to be more in the form \Nof entertainment than anything else, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.46,0:40:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with music \Nand very colorful characters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.70,0:40:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we were \Nto say in our heart, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.97,0:40:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I hope that idiot \Ndoesn’t get into power,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.44,0:40:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,are we neutral? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.47,0:41:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Or worse still, if we say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.51,0:41:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I hope the other person \Ngets into power,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.55,0:41:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,well, we need \Nto be careful, don’t we? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.91,0:41:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember many years ago \Nas a young pioneer in Australia, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.42,0:41:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was facing \Nthe conscription issue\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.72,0:41:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,—the national call-up \Nfor the military. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.22,0:41:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, \Nthe Vietnam War was being fought. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.26,0:41:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there was \Nan election in Australia. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.03,0:41:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that time, the party \Nthat was trying to get into power\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.83,0:41:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,said that if they got into power, \Nthey would abolish conscription. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.17,0:41:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So now that affected me personally. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.61,0:41:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember how hard it was sitting there \Nwatching the election results, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.21,0:41:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,not to say in my heart, \N‘I hope they get in.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.51,0:41:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, when they got in, \Nnot to say, ‘Yes!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.15,0:41:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if we personally are affected \Nby some of these political promises, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.49,0:41:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we may violate our neutrality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.86,0:41:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So brothers and sisters, \Nlet’s work hard at remembering \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.67,0:41:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that we’re no part of this world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.67,0:42:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We support the best government \Nthat could ever rule this earth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.24,0:42:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And by doing so, \Nwe will keep our neutrality, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.27,0:42:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and we will keep our unity.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.84,0:42:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When neutrality is mentioned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.85,0:42:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,isn’t it true we often think of taking \Na stand during times of war? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.72,0:42:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But Brother Jackson \Nreminded us that neutrality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.85,0:42:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is something we do every day \Nin our thoughts and in our speech. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.33,0:42:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What a good example \Nof analyzing a Bible principle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.36,0:42:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand its full meaning \Nand application for us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.20,0:42:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, \Nthere are times when governments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.00,0:42:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,do pressure God’s people \Nto renounce their faith or take up arms. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.34,0:42:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This happened \Nto Sister Gertrud Pötzinger \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.14,0:42:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and her husband, Martin, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.14,0:42:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in Nazi Germany \Nduring World War II. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.41,0:42:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, later in life, Brother Pötzinger \Nwas a member of the Governing Body, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.12,0:42:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and he finished \Nhis earthly course in 1988; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.65,0:42:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but Sister Pötzinger continued \Nfaithful until her death in 2003. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.66,0:43:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In an archived interview, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.73,0:43:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Pötzinger described \Nher wartime experiences. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.47,0:43:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Gertrud and Martin, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.63,0:43:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,like thousands \Nof our spiritual brothers and sisters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.17,0:43:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,keep their integrity \Nthrough brutal persecution?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.21,0:43:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked underground \Nand traveled in Silesia, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.75,0:43:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and at that time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.08,0:43:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I visited the families \Nwith copies of The Watchtower. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.42,0:43:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They caught me and arrested me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.22,0:43:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in Dresden.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.13,0:43:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And there, there was\Nthe same strong interrogation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.70,0:43:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah helped me \Nin a wonderful way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.60,0:43:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was surprised by myself\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.00,0:43:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,—what kind of thoughts \Ncame in my mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.31,0:43:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,when they asked me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.41,0:43:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“Did you know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.51,0:43:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“that the organization \Nof the Watchtower \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.61,0:43:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is forbidden \Nby the government?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.45,0:43:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I was saying, \N“Sure, I know that.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.99,0:44:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why were you \Nworking underground \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.89,0:44:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,against our command?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.69,0:44:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I was saying: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.73,0:44:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“The German judgment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.93,0:44:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“they acknowledge the command: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.17,0:44:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘You have not to steal, \Nnot to lie, not to murder.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.74,0:44:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“And this came from the Mosaic Law; \Nit’s from the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.78,0:44:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“If you acknowledge \Nthis command, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.98,0:44:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“then you have to acknowledge \Nthe other command too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.08,0:44:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Bible is saying: \N‘You have to watch \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.72,0:44:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“to come together \N and to encourage one another.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.52,0:44:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“How can I do it \Nif I would be ashamed to meet them? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.36,0:44:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“I want to do the will of God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.70,0:44:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a commandment.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.16,0:44:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The judge was saying nothing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.20,0:44:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He spoke with the side judge, \Nbut he gave no answer.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.77,0:44:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sentenced \Nat first for five years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.08,0:44:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And later on, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.21,0:44:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,they made it go down \Nto three and a half years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.35,0:45:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was so young; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.38,0:45:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I was 25 years of age. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.42,0:45:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So I started \Nmy solitary confinement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.39,0:45:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah’s spirit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.33,0:45:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,made me real joyful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.26,0:45:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day \NI was thinking: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.27,0:45:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Now I have \Nto make every day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.97,0:45:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,‘a special object \Nto think about. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.74,0:45:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,‘In fact, \NI want to think \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.91,0:45:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,about the qualities \Nof Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.15,0:45:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll start with wisdom.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.08,0:45:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I put \Nmy fingers in my ears \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.38,0:45:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and was running \Nto and fro and to and fro. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.69,0:45:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted \Nto hear nothing outside. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.39,0:45:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, wonderful thoughts \Nand I was happy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.76,0:45:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Then when that was over, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.83,0:45:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,then I thought: \N‘What is hope? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.87,0:45:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What is faith?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.87,0:46:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I started to think \Nabout the fruits of the spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.34,0:46:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a lot. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.61,0:46:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I have \Nso much to think, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.55,0:46:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the time runs.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.92,0:46:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,After three and a half years, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.29,0:46:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the Gestapo \Ncalled me again \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.66,0:46:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and gave me \Na declaration. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.86,0:46:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to sign \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.86,0:46:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that I never want \Nto be in connection \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.93,0:46:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Jehovah’s Witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.00,0:46:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and that I refuse \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.00,0:46:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn more \Nfrom the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.63,0:46:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said: \N“No! Never!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.64,0:46:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he said, \N“You can think for overnight.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.11,0:46:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“No! \NI want not to think overnight.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.41,0:46:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And immediately I said: \N“Never will I do it! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.21,0:46:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Never will I sign it!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.48,0:46:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he was saying: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.12,0:46:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then you have \Nto take the consequences. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.42,0:46:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“You will transfer \Nto the concentration camp\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.89,0:46:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,—to Ravensbruck.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.66,0:46:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I came, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.70,0:46:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,they ordered that I have \Nto put all my dress out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.70,0:47:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and to get them away. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.57,0:47:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I have to stay \Nwith other prisoners \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.81,0:47:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,several hours \Nin a big bedroom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.64,0:47:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have to wait \Ntill the doctor will see us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.78,0:47:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was \Nso humiliating. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.75,0:47:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They wanted to humiliate, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.96,0:47:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and they wanted \Nto make us down. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.56,0:47:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And the old women \Nbetween the young girls, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.33,0:47:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,they were  so strongly ashamed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.33,0:47:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw it\N—how they suffered.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.21,0:47:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I never will forget this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.21,0:47:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And after, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.45,0:47:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we got the new dress \Nfrom the camp \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.99,0:47:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and we were assigned to go \Nto the punishment barrack. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.16,0:47:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then \Nthat was a terrible night. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.96,0:48:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So many prisoners, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.00,0:48:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,they were crying the night \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.16,0:48:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and others were vomiting\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.50,0:48:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,—had to vomit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.41,0:48:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a terrible night. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.74,0:48:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, \Nwe had to go for working. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.25,0:48:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We had so strong to work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.55,0:48:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,from morning\N—in summertime, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.55,0:48:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,from 5 o’clock \Nwe were on the roll call place \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.09,0:48:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,till evening, 7 o’clock. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.82,0:48:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the quarantine came. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.86,0:48:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to not go out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.63,0:48:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They closed the door. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.00,0:48:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They gave us our meals \Nthrough the window, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.47,0:48:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and we had \Na fine time to have rest. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.20,0:48:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We encouraged one another \Nwith spiritual interests. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.24,0:48:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And the doctor came \Nand knocked on the window. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.51,0:48:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“Who died in your barrack?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.51,0:48:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“Nobody.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.51,0:48:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.25,0:48:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Our old, weak sisters \Nthey overcame all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.82,0:49:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Never some became sick. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.39,0:49:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was really a good witness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.43,0:49:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for the others in the camp.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.23,0:49:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband was \Nin the concentration camp, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.93,0:49:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,at first in Dachau \Nand later on in Mauthausen.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.67,0:49:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They worked \Nin the stone quarry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.17,0:49:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that group, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.31,0:49:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a brother \Nhad the bad shoes; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.25,0:49:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they were too tight for him, \Nand he took them off. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.28,0:49:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And he had forgotten \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.89,0:49:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to take them from the stone quarry \Nto the camp. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.96,0:49:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And my husband \Nwanted to help him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.79,0:49:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was running \Nto pick up the shoes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.66,0:49:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And the watchman \Nobserved that he \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.23,0:49:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,ran away from the lawn, \Nfrom the group. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.34,0:49:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,His punishment was to hang \Nfor one hour on the pole. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.17,0:49:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When I asked my husband, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.14,0:50:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“How did you overcome \Nsuch a torture?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.81,0:50:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he said: \N“I was thinking: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.15,0:50:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘How was the situation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.12,0:50:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘when Abraham \Nhad to kill his son? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.76,0:50:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“And this was a long way.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.76,0:50:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“I was always thinking: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.76,0:50:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘What were his thoughts? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.76,0:50:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘How had he \Novercome his feeling \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.13,0:50:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and what Jehovah \Nwants for him?’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.20,0:50:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this way, \Nhe didn’t feel anymore. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.81,0:50:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,After one hour, \Nwhen he came down, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.81,0:50:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the other brothers \Nwere saying, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.98,0:50:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“You don’t look as you have been \Non the torture stake.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.95,0:50:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah can help us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.49,0:50:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in all such situations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.62,0:50:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Every situation we had some \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.46,0:50:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of what was not so easy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.30,0:50:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But in every situation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.03,0:50:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a touch of wonderful help\N—Jehovah’s spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.44,0:50:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And we could pray. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.51,0:51:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s name \Nis the most important part in our life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.21,0:51:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is so important \Nlike Jehovah’s name.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.62,0:51:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see the ways Jehovah blessed \NSister Pötzinger’s determination \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.46,0:51:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to stay loyal under pressure? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.06,0:51:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,At Matthew 10:19, \NJesus told his apostles: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.23,0:51:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“When they hand you over, \Ndo not become anxious \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.30,0:51:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“about how or what \Nyou are to speak, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.20,0:51:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,for what you are to speak \Nwill be given you in that hour.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.54,0:51:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She may have felt that same assurance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.54,0:51:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when arrested and interrogated. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.71,0:51:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, when tested in the camps, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.71,0:51:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,she and Martin meditated \Non Christian qualities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.45,0:51:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the faith of Bible characters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.82,0:51:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally they, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.82,0:51:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,like so many Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.82,0:51:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,were helped to survive \Nbecause of the love and care \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.72,0:51:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of their spiritual brothers and sisters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.16,0:51:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Pötzinger used her experience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.50,0:51:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to encourage others \Nin her later assignments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.83,0:51:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in the interview \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.83,0:52:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,with William and Sandra Malenfant, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.84,0:52:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Malenfant remembered working \Nwith Sister Pötzinger \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.47,0:52:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Bethel Sewing Department, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.47,0:52:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and Sister Pötzinger had given her \Na memorable sewing illustration. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.81,0:52:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She likened each prayer \Nto adding another thread \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.22,0:52:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to a strong cord \Nthat unites us with Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.79,0:52:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You might enjoy \Nwatching that interview again \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.62,0:52:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in the “Interviews and Experiences” section,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.42,0:52:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,under “Blessings of Sacred Service.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.99,0:52:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Later this month, \Nyou’ll also want to watch \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.76,0:52:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a new original song \Nunder the “Music” section. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.63,0:52:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In the April 2016 program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.10,0:52:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,a group of young ones explained \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.97,0:52:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,why they visited Bethel \Nand what they enjoyed seeing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.64,0:52:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,While there, they also sang \Na song about their experience, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.51,0:52:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with the help of Bethelites, \Nat the branches they visited.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.82,0:52:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have a music video \Nto enjoy in this month’s program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.69,0:52:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s called \NStop, Think, and Pray. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.69,0:53:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what the problem is, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.03,0:53:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we should always take time \Nto think about Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.97,0:53:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and pray for Jehovah’s holy spirit.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.88,0:53:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Life’s not easy when trouble’s around\NAnd the whole situation is getting you down.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.92,0:53:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So-called friends, they just want a reaction.\NTurn to Jehovah and pray—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.43,0:53:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Silently pray.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.11,0:53:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t give up; don’t give in.\NPut your trust in Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.45,0:54:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it calm; we can win\NIf we stop, think, and pray.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.26,0:54:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When there seems no way out,\NHe’ll be there, always by our side.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.44,0:54:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He will be our guide, never doubt;\NNo, just stop, think, and pray.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.51,0:54:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Make Jehovah smile.\NLet him show the way.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.30,0:54:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ev’ry day will have troubles to share.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.50,0:54:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There are bills to be paid \Nwith no money to spare.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.74,0:55:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, we’ll be happy in giving\NIf we can make someone smile—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.99,0:55:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Make someone smile.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.06,0:55:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Never doubt; never fear.\NPut your trust in Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.77,0:55:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And our road will be clear\NIf we stop, think, and pray.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.68,0:55:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When we’re weak, we are strong.\NAnd we’ll see he was by our side.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.19,0:55:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He has been our guide all along.\NAlways stop, think, and pray.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.20,0:56:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Make Jehovah smile.\NLet him show the way.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.31,0:56:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your trust in Jehovah.\NAnd our road will be clear\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.16,0:56:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If we stop, think, and pray.\NWhen we’re weak, we are strong.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.63,0:56:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll see he was by our side.\NHe has been our guide all along.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.68,0:56:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Always stop, think, and pray.\NMake Jehovah smile.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.65,0:56:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank him ev’ry day.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.19,0:56:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will always bless us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.36,0:56:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,when we go to him \Nin prayer with our concerns. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.70,0:56:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever the situation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.70,0:57:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,he can give us \N“the power beyond what is normal.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.90,0:57:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we learned \Nand practiced in this program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.54,0:57:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we do our part by training \Nour “power of reason” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.24,0:57:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,with the principles \Nfrom his written Word.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.01,0:57:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, \Nwe have greetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.15,0:57:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Vesterålen islands, \Nin Norway.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.38,0:57:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,These islands are home to 30,000 people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.49,0:57:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,who enjoy the beautiful fjords, mountains, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.16,0:57:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and calm beaches.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.89,0:57:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The 53 publishers \Nin the Sortland Norwegian Congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.73,0:57:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,preach in a territory that covers \N1,800 square kilometers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.53,0:57:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or 695 square miles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.24,0:57:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Their thorough witnessing takes them \Ninto the beautiful countryside, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.71,0:57:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as to the city of Sortland \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.71,0:57:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for metropolitan public witnessing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.65,0:57:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Each year, they organize trips \Nto unassigned territory, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.18,0:57:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,where they often meet people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.09,0:57:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who show deep respect for the Bible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.19,0:57:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One Saturday each month, \Nafter the ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.92,0:58:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they gather to watch \Nthe JW Broadcasting program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.13,0:58:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and enjoy spending time together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.30,0:58:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Progressive Bible studies \Nand a Russian group \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.27,0:58:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,join them each week \Nat their meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.94,0:58:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We send our love \Nand greetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.07,0:58:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and thank them \Nfor their Christian love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.87,0:58:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and example of faith.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.94,0:58:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for watching. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.95,0:58:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,From the world headquarters \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.52,0:58:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting!\N
